<h2>RESPONSIBILITIES</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Write and produce accurate, high-quality materials ranging from compelling monthly e-newsletters and&nbsp;blogs for national distribution to social media campaigns and other online material.</li>
  <li>Build and execute social media strategy for PACER's various social media accounts. Generate, edit, and publish content on a regular basis that builds meaningful connections and encourages community action.</li>
  <li>Conduct interviews and write with accuracy and speed about people&rsquo;s personal experiences as well as complex legislative and public policy issues. </li>
  <li>Edit content, style, and design of print and online material.</li>
  <li>Learn Individuals with Disabilities Education ACT (IDEA) and disability related content.</li>
  <li>Contribute to respected state and national media relations through contacting media outlets, writing news releases, publicizing special events, providing reports with reliable sources and interacting with the press. </li>
  <li>Oversee PACER&rsquo;s various websites to keep content current.</li>
  <li>Photograph individuals and events.</li>
  <li>Collaborate with PACER staff on conceptualizing and developing online and print publications</li>
  <li>Market and promote PACER programs and materials</li>
  <li>Other duties as may be assigned.</li>
</ol>
<h2 style="margin-top:30px;"><strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong></h2>
<ul>
      <li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in communications, journalism, or similar field</li>
      <li>Experience preferred in writing for newspapers or news-oriented periodicals </li>
      <li>Knowledge and experience in Associated Press style</li>
      <li>Knowledge of &ldquo;family friendly&rdquo; language</li>
      <li>Comfort in initiating contact with media and press about relevant topics</li>
      <li>Attend PACER workshops to learn content</li>
      <li>Occasional press related evening and weekend work</li>
      <li>Working knowledge of graphic design and print production</li>
      <li>Ability to manage several projects at once while adhering to deadlines</li>
      <li>Ability to adapt styles of writing to varied audiences</li>
      <li>Strong organizational skills and attention to detail</li>
      <li>Assertiveness in initiating new projects&nbsp;</li>
      <li>Ability to think creatively</li>
      <li>Ability to work independently as well as in team planning and decision-making</li>
      <li>Must have interpersonal skills that encourage cooperation when editing other writer&rsquo;s work</li>
      <li>Knowledge of and sensitivity to issues experienced by persons with disabilities</li>
</ul>
<p>Parents of children  with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
  Salary to be determined based on experience. Position available immediately.</p>
